The paper deals with bandit algorithms, which are commonly studied in the machine learning subfield of reinforcement learning (cs.LG). The specific application of the wireless network selection problem falls under the subfield of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and the paper also discusses the use of information theory (cs.IT) in the analysis of the algorithms. The problem of adapting to a dynamic environment is relevant to the subfield of control systems (cs.SY), and the use of algorithms to make decisions and learn from data is relevant to the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
